-- Ghana central bank says to ease forex rules it imposed in Feb
-- By Kwasi Kpodo
-- Thu Jun 12, 2014 11:31AM EDT
-- None



ACCRA, June 12 (Reuters) - Ghana's central bank is to ease restrictions it imposed in February on foreign exchange transactions in a bid to halt a slide in the cedi <GHS=> currency, governor Henry Kofi Wampah told Reuters on Thursday.

